items.name: LockTokens
lines: Each lock token is a URI.

items.name: Owner
lines: This element provides information sufficient for either directly contacting a principal (such as a telephone number or email URI), or for discovering the principal (such as the URL of a homepage) who owns the lock.

items.name: Timeout
lines: a timeout value for the lock.

This element specifies the number of seconds between granting of the lock and the automatic removal of that lock. The value must not be greater than 2^32-1. A value of -1 stands for an infinite lock, that will never be removed automatically.
